reviews.review_text: As Strong As They Get 5 Stars for the sound alone.  Easily could be passed off as a Matrix.  Outstanding.  That and unlike the SBD's up here, you get the whole show.  Jerry is just playing like liquid fire from start to finish. Most definitely a very, very high recommendation on this one.  Very much worth a listen.

Pitch It's unfortunate that with all the work that I'm sure goes into making these tapes available to us (which I am grateful for)  so often the issue of pitch correction is not considered before the release.  Some apparently don't notice or care and this recording would sound wonderful for those people. For me however it is a glaring defect that makes it unlistenable.

pitch corr Its funny how peple talk about pitch... You listen to it and tel me the fix. As I here this the boys were out of tune most of the show. AS well any speed issues are transient over the length of tape and are very if not impossible to fix with one liniar speed change.

In reality speed issues many times are not linear in nature and change as the take up reels on the decks fill or empty. The tork necessary to keep stable varies. Most decks capstan motors are not prepared to deal with this.... The motors in the deck used are some of the largest there are so any speed issues are not with play back...

Fixing the pitch/ speed is subjective and not strait forward on this recording. We felt and still feel that the Document speaks for itself.. As it will remain un-listenable to some here... Well... That is there loss. :-)

aegert

the pitch O K, there are a few slurrs and the volcals sometimes do fade-away but hell this is a must to listen to,it,s a 73 concert!!!the sound recording is great and jerry's is just tearing it up.i know you rider>chiniaCat is really hot and Playin in the band,is wow!thanks for the great show.

Must Stream Fantastic aud of prime '73 material.  the second set jam while not interstellar like 5.26 or some of 11.10,11.14, 11.17 - this is a great second set.  ALso wanted to thank A Egert for the good work the team put in on this and for clarifying for people what truly causes pitch issues and that they are not always linear in nature. Us mid-'80's tour heads love the work the foldks do on the IA.  This is a Must Stream show.

High quality AUD As a mid to late 80s taper who got to enjoy such things as a "tapers' section," kudos to those pioneers who made tapes like this one in the days before tapers' sections! 

This is a dandy. The vocals may not be as crisp as one would like, but the instrumentation is all there with presence, snap, and sparkle.

Oh yeah, pitch? Sounds like the pitch is pretty good to me.

Thanks to all who make these recordings available.
